        {
          "bbox": [
            31.19,
            107.27,
            564.11,
            134.79
          ],
          "text": "Subjective Observations: Patient reports continued pain in lower extremities, particularly at night. Reports good adherence to\nmedication regimen and diet.  Patient reports occasionally feeling dizzy.",
          "char_count": 200
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            31.19,
            141.29,
            564.11,
            168.8
          ],
          "text": "Assesment: Patient remains stable with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus and peripheral neuropathy. Glucose control is within target range,\nbut neuropathy symptoms persist.  Dizziness could be related to medication or blood pressure; further investigation warranted.",
          "char_count": 257
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            31.19,
            175.3,
            564.09,
            202.82
          ],
          "text": "Recommendations: Continue current medication regimen. Monitor blood glucose levels regularly. Start taking blood pressure at\nhome. Consider referral to physical therapy for neuropathy. Rule out medication-related dizziness.",
          "char_count": 223
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            31.19,
            209.32,
            564.1,
            236.83
          ],
          "text": "Follow Up Instruction: Follow-up appointment in 3 months. Schedule ECG and peripheral nerve conduction study. Contact clinic if\ndizziness worsens or new symptoms develop.",
          "char_count": 170
        },
        {
